                            <comment id="12924198" author="janhoy" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2010 14:35:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch shows the 2nd level parsers and their mimetypes instead of listing all the mimetypes directly below the CompositeParser.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12927705" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 01:05:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch.&lt;br/&gt;
Prints true name of parser even if wrapped in ParserDecorator.&lt;br/&gt;
Uses recursion to support n-levels of composite parsers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12927713" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 01:16:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new patch prints all levels including the top level:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
lap:target janhoy$ java -jar tika-app-0.8-SNAPSHOT.jar --list-parser-details
org.apache.tika.parser.AutoDetectParser (Composite Parser):
  org.apache.tika.parser.DefaultParser (Composite Parser):
    org.apache.tika.parser.asm.ClassParser
      application/java-vm
    org.apache.tika.parser.audio.AudioParser
      audio/x-aiff
      audio/x-wav
      audio/basic
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This gives a more true picture of how things are wired than the old format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Candidate for 0.8 ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
